HOUSE BILL 1143
J1 6lr1173
By: Delegates Lopez, Alston, Behler, Crutchfield, Feldmark, D. Jones, Lehman,
Martinez, Palakovich Carr, Patterson, Shetty, Spiegel, Terrasa,
White Holland, Wilkins, Wims, Wolek, and Woorman
Introduced and read first time: February 11, 2026
Assigned to: Health
A BILL ENTITLED
1 AN ACT concerning
2 Public Health – Office of the Chief Medical Examiner – Perinatal Autopsies
3 (Lung Float Test Ban)
4 FOR the purpose of prohibiting the Chief Medical Examiner, deputy chief medical
5 examiners, assistant medical examiners, and pathologists authorized by the Chief
6 Medical Examiner from using a hydrostatic lung test, also known as a lung float test,
7 if performing a certain perinatal autopsy; authorizing a parent, guardian, or legal
8 representative to bring a civil action for a violation of certain provisions of this Act;
9 altering the grounds for discipline of a physician to include a violation of certain
10 provisions of this Act; and generally relating to the Office of the Chief Medical
11 Examiner and perinatal autopsies.
12 BY repealing and reenacting, with amendments,
